&lt;p&gt;SO, YOU’RE GREAT… AND WE’RE GREAT. FANCY WORKING TOGETHER?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Hull University Teaching Hospitals NHS Trust we’ve created great careers so great people like you can join us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking to recruit a B6 Specialist Renal Dietitian and this post is ideal for any Dietitian looking to develop their skills within renal medicine as a full training and support package is provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As well as providing dietetic services to the acute kidney unit at Hull Royal Infirmary, you’ll get great experience in all areas of renal medicine including transplant, peritoneal dialysis, haemodialyis, pre dialysis, and general nephrology. So, if we like each other you’ll join a supportive, award winning and forward thinking team providing great services in a large teaching centre with first class facilities. The renal dietetic team are the 2019 Golden Heart winners of the Team Spirit award.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hull was the UK’s City of Culture for 2017 and was recently rated by Rough Guide as one of the top ten tourist destinations in the world. An underestimated city that is a hub for music festivals, nightlife, restaurants, theatres and bars, with world class visitor attractions and famous sports teams, this is a great and affordable place to work, play, live and unwind.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us, you’ll love it. We Promise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;** Salary relates to year 3 of 3 year NHS pay deal&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PLEASE NOTE: In cases where a vacancy receives a high number of applications, we may bring the closing date forward. You are therefore advised to get in quick!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Need a chat or want to visit? Telephone 01482 674707 or email Katherine Durrans (Dietetic Team Leader) &lt;span&gt;Katherine.Durrans@hey.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
